@startuml fig-mqtt-pub-sub
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title MQTT Publish/Subscribe Model

participant "Publisher\n(sensor)" as pub #FFE0B2
participant "MQTT Broker\n(Mosquitto)" as broker #E1BEE7
participant "Subscriber A\n(actuator)" as subA #C8E6C9
participant "Subscriber B\n(dashboard)" as subB #BBDEFB

== SUBSCRIPTION PHASE ==

subA -> broker : SUBSCRIBE\ntopic: sensors/temperature
broker --> subA : SUBACK

subB -> broker : SUBSCRIBE\ntopic: sensors/temperature
broker --> subB : SUBACK

== PUBLISH PHASE ==

pub -> broker : PUBLISH\ntopic: sensors/temperature\npayload: 27.5

broker -[#43A047]-> subA : DELIVER\npayload: 27.5
broker -[#1565C0]-> subB : DELIVER\npayload: 27.5

== DECOUPLED OPERATION ==

pub -> broker : PUBLISH\ntopic: sensors/temperature\npayload: 31.2

broker -[#43A047]-> subA : DELIVER\npayload: 31.2
broker -[#1565C0]-> subB : DELIVER\npayload: 31.2

legend right
The broker matches topics and routes
messages to all active subscribers.
Publishers and subscribers are fully
decoupled — neither knows the other.
QoS levels control delivery guarantees.
endlegend
@enduml
